5.	Health Sync:
o	Apple HealthKit (iOS), Health Connect / Google Fit / Fitbit
6.	AI Assistant:
‚Ä¢	Google Gemini API (via Firebase AI Logic or server-side SDK)
üì¶ Dataset Access Reference
1.  Air Quality (PM2.5, PM10, O‚ÇÉ, NO‚ÇÇ)
‚Ä¢	US Primary: AirNow / EPA AQS
o	API key required (AirNow); AQS is public
o	JSON format; includes AQI categories
o	Use lat/lon + NowCast for nearest station
‚Ä¢	Global Open: OpenAQ
o	REST API (v3); bulk data via S3
‚Ä¢	Paid Fallback: IQAir / AirVisual
‚Ä¢	API key plans; includes forecasts
Integration Tips:
‚Ä¢	Query AirNow/AQS first ‚Üí fallback to OpenAQ/IQAir if no station
‚Ä¢	Cache responses per location (5‚Äì15 min)
2. üî• Wildfire / Smoke Indicators
‚Ä¢	NASA FIRMS: MODIS/VIIRS fire detections
‚Ä¢	NOAA HMS / HYSPLIT: Smoke dispersion & forecasting
Integration Tips:
‚Ä¢	Combine FIRMS fire points + NOAA smoke models
‚Ä¢	If both show activity ‚Üí elevate smoke alert
3. ‚ò¢Ô∏è Radon Context (US)
‚Ä¢	EPA Radon Zone Maps: Lookup by ZIP/county
‚Ä¢	Outside US: Use geological survey APIs or public studies
Integration Tips:
‚Ä¢	Radon = static background context
‚Ä¢	Display as weekly tile + link to testing resources
4. üöó Traffic Data
‚Ä¢	TomTom: Reliable, moderate pricing
‚Ä¢	HERE: Generous free tier
‚Ä¢	Google Maps: High quality, expensive
Integration Tips:
‚Ä¢	Use traffic data to infer NO‚ÇÇ hotspots
‚Ä¢	Precompute for saved places; minimize API calls
5.  Weather Data
‚Ä¢	OpenWeatherMap: Easy free tier
‚Ä¢	NOAA / Meteomatics / Weatherbit: Production-grade
Integration Tips:
‚Ä¢	Poll hourly; cache results
‚Ä¢	Normalize units (SI or imperial)
6.  Health-Synced Data
‚Ä¢	Apple HealthKit: Local device store; user consent
‚Ä¢	Google Health Connect / Fit / Fitbit: Cloud access via OAuth
Auth & Privacy:
‚Ä¢	Use OAuth2 where needed
‚Ä¢	Encrypt locally; minimize data storage
‚Ä¢	Evaluate HIPAA compliance for clinical data
7. üìç Location / GPS
‚Ä¢	Native APIs: iOS CoreLocation / Android FusedLocationProvider
‚Ä¢	Use coordinates for air/smoke/weather queries
Integration Tips:
‚Ä¢	Allow manual pinning + reverse geocoding (TomTom/HERE/Google Places)
8. üì∂ Bluetooth (BLE)
‚Ä¢	Prefer platform hubs (HealthKit, Health Connect, Fitbit)
‚Ä¢	If direct BLE: implement BLE Central, subscribe to notifications
Integration Tips:
‚Ä¢	BLE = high QA complexity ‚Üí Tier-3 unless device is owned
9.   AI API (Gemini API)
‚Ä¢	Gemini API: Use server-side SDK or Firebase AI Logic
‚Ä¢	Ideal for interpretation, personalization ‚Äî not clinical inference
‚Ä¢	Use the AI for interpretation (one-sentence rationale, personalized tips), not for heavy clinical inference without medical review
